                                                             LINUX ADMINISTRARTION BASICS



 1> Hostname: the name of a linux computer or server.

   command: hostname 

     it display the hostname (name) of the current linux system.


  2> date & time: it display current date and time of system
   

     command: date
    


   3> disk usage: displays total disk space, used space, free space, and usage percentage in RAM 
    

     command: df -h
  

     du -sh <file or folder name> : this ccommand show size of file or folder .



   df -h : its show entire disk storage usage.

   du -sh <file or folder name> : it show size os specific file or directory.
  


   4> memory usage 

     free -h: this command display total,used,and available memory in RAM



   5> shutdown
    
     sudo shutdown now: this command use for safely shutdown the linux system


    6> reboot
    
      sudo reboot: restart the linux system 
     
  
